properties.areaDesc: San Diego County Mountains; Riverside County Mountains
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 10 at 2:01PM PST until February 10 at 4:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow occurring. Additional snow accumulations of one inch
expected for the Riverside County Mountains. Additional
accumulations of 2 to 4 inches expected in the San Diego County
Mountains.

* WHERE...The Mountains of Riverside and San Diego Counties
above 5000 feet. Heaviest at the higher elevations of the San
Diego County Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 4 PM today.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Be prepared for reduced visibilities at
times. Plan on difficult travel conditions,
including during the morning commute. Tree branches could fall
as well.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow means periods of snow will
cause primarily travel difficulties. Be prepared for snow covered
roads and limited visibilities, and use caution while driving.

For road condition information in California...enter
8 0 0 4 2 7 7 6 2 3 if inside california or
9 1 6 4 5 5 7 6 2 3 if outside California.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON ABOVE 5000 FEET
